/* 
=============================================================================
SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
=============================================================================

PREREQUISITES:
1. Install Node.js (v14 or higher) from https://nodejs.org/
2. Install MongoDB Community Server from https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community

INSTALLATION STEPS:

1. CREATE PROJECT FOLDER:
   mkdir educational-website
   cd educational-website

2. CREATE FILES:
   - Create "server.js" with the backend code
   - Create "package.json" with this content
   - Create a folder named "public"
   - Create "index.html" inside the "public" folder with the frontend code

3. INSTALL DEPENDENCIES:
   npm install

4. START MONGODB:
   
   Windows:
   - MongoDB should start automatically as a service
   - Or manually: "C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\[version]\bin\mongod.exe"
   
   Mac (using Homebrew):
   brew services start mongodb-community
   
   Linux:
   sudo systemctl start mongod

5. START THE SERVER:
   npm start
   
   (Or for development with auto-restart: npm run dev)

6. ACCESS THE WEBSITE:
   Open your browser and navigate to:
   http://localhost:3000

FOLDER STRUCTURE:
educational-website/
├── server.js
├── package.json
└── public/
    └── index.html

TROUBLESHOOTING:

- If MongoDB connection fails:
  * Ensure MongoDB is running (check Task Manager/Activity Monitor)
  * Verify MongoDB is running on default port 27017
  * Try: mongod --dbpath /path/to/data/directory

- If port 3000 is already in use:
  * Change PORT value in server.js (line 7)
  * Update the fetch URL in index.html accordingly

- If modules don't load:
  * Check browser console (F12) for errors
  * Verify server is running (check terminal)
  * Ensure CORS is enabled in server.js

FEATURES:
- Five educational modules covering software testing and development
- MongoDB backend for data persistence
- Clean, responsive design
- Easy navigation between modules
- Automatic data initialization on first run

=============================================================================
*/
